1
00:00:09,100 --> 00:00:14,000
(This program is intended for mature audiences.
It may feature explicit content, violence, and strong language)

2
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:20,075
(All characters, places, and events
in this series are entirely fictitious)

3
00:00:38,425 --> 00:00:40,300
You said you wouldn't
go public, didn't you?

4
00:00:44,859 --> 00:00:46,151
I'm Wayu's boyfriend.

5
00:00:51,526 --> 00:00:52,526
Krit.

6
00:00:53,235 --> 00:00:55,152
But this is right in the middle
of my workplace, you know.

7
00:00:57,256 --> 00:00:58,777
Then why are you acting so possessive?

8
00:01:06,966 --> 00:01:07,966
I'm sorry.

9
00:01:09,195 --> 00:01:10,904
If you'll excuse us, I need to get
my boyfriend home.

10
00:01:14,011 --> 00:01:16,634
(Call for champagne)

11
00:01:21,488 --> 00:01:24,405
Keeping after someone even after they've
clearly rejected you multiple times

12
00:01:25,239 --> 00:01:26,530
isn't nice.

13
00:01:28,385 --> 00:01:29,510
I don't mind

14
00:01:30,427 --> 00:01:31,823
as long as a friend stays a friend.

15
00:01:37,073 --> 00:01:39,782
- Krit.
- Send him away.

16
00:01:40,178 --> 00:01:41,991
- Why do something like this?
- Go.

17
00:01:41,991 --> 00:01:42,741
Ouch.

18
00:01:42,741 --> 00:01:44,407
Go walk the customer out.

19
00:01:44,407 --> 00:01:45,762
- Okay.
- Please go ahead.

20
00:01:45,762 --> 00:01:47,241
- Let's go, Mind.
- Mind, let's go.

21
00:01:47,241 --> 00:01:49,512
Then I'll walk you to your car.
Take it slow.

22
00:01:49,554 --> 00:01:54,450
=Love of Silom=

23
00:01:57,805 --> 00:02:00,805
Maybe you should quit this job.
What do you think, Wayu?

24
00:02:08,723 --> 00:02:09,702
Why is that?

25
00:02:16,182 --> 00:02:17,329
Are you jealous of me?

26
00:02:22,930 --> 00:02:26,849
Hmm? What happened to Captain Krit,
the stern officer

27
00:02:26,849 --> 00:02:29,894
who was so good at keeping
official secrets? Hmm?

28
00:02:30,367 --> 00:02:33,138
Don't change the subject.
That's a different issue.

29
00:02:34,228 --> 00:02:35,241
Hey.

30
00:02:39,753 --> 00:02:40,976
Hey.

31
00:02:44,837 --> 00:02:45,774
Ugh.

32
00:02:49,215 --> 00:02:50,133
Krit.

33
00:02:50,955 --> 00:02:53,574
I don't want you feeling
that way either.

34
00:02:54,740 --> 00:02:59,136
But if you're asking me to quit this job,
I can't really do that yet.

35
00:03:01,354 --> 00:03:04,355
So I'm the one who has to change.

36
00:03:05,712 --> 00:03:09,707
From now on, I'll be more clear
about my boundaries with customers.

37
00:03:10,377 --> 00:03:11,791
So you don't have to worry.

38
00:03:12,479 --> 00:03:13,225
Hmm?

39
00:03:15,997 --> 00:03:17,258
That would be nice.

40
00:03:19,915 --> 00:03:20,967
But honestly,

41
00:03:24,752 --> 00:03:26,625
I don't like sharing Wayu with anyone.

42
00:03:30,812 --> 00:03:33,526
Who are you sharing with? Hmm?

43
00:03:34,864 --> 00:03:36,527
I'm yours alone.

44
00:03:38,401 --> 00:03:39,529
Really.

45
00:03:43,772 --> 00:03:44,805
- Hmm.
- Mmm.

46
00:03:47,003 --> 00:03:48,303
- Hmm.
- Mmm.

47
00:03:52,489 --> 00:03:53,407
Hey.

48
00:03:57,651 --> 00:03:58,511
Mm.

49
00:04:00,843 --> 00:04:01,627
Mm.

50
00:04:02,755 --> 00:04:03,844
Mm.

51
00:05:19,964 --> 00:05:23,062
(Foei Moonlit: Call me tomorrow.
I need to talk to you)

52
00:05:44,414 --> 00:05:45,198
Hey.

53
00:05:47,549 --> 00:05:48,849
Aren't you going to work today?

54
00:05:50,378 --> 00:05:52,194
I'm waiting to have breakfast
with you first.

55
00:05:53,551 --> 00:05:56,553
Hmm, spoiling me like this?

56
00:05:56,954 --> 00:05:58,464
Because you feel bad about last night?

57
00:05:59,974 --> 00:06:03,396
Yeah, something like that.

58
00:06:05,537 --> 00:06:07,946
I broke the rules
of being a host's boyfriend.

59
00:06:11,004 --> 00:06:14,025
Captain, you have only one flaw.

60
00:06:14,025 --> 00:06:16,204
You just never say what you really feel.

61
00:06:27,158 --> 00:06:28,113
Whoa.

62
00:06:30,044 --> 00:06:33,944
Oh, it's fine. I'll have the maid
clean it up.

63
00:06:35,932 --> 00:06:38,398
- Wow.
- Come here.

64
00:06:39,468 --> 00:06:40,386
Come on.

65
00:06:45,624 --> 00:06:46,675
Let's have a taste.

66
00:06:53,958 --> 00:06:54,723
Ahem.

67
00:06:56,367 --> 00:06:57,380
You don't like it?

68
00:06:59,177 --> 00:07:01,414
I do. It's really good.

69
00:07:01,853 --> 00:07:05,964
I'm just not used to the flavor yet.

70
00:07:05,964 --> 00:07:11,622
It's clean, healthy cooking,
like a mom's touch.

71
00:07:14,107 --> 00:07:15,330
So that means it's not good?

72
00:07:17,452 --> 00:07:19,268
No. It's good.

73
00:07:20,033 --> 00:07:23,359
Here, I'll show you.
I could eat this all day, seriously.

74
00:07:23,626 --> 00:07:24,468
Whoa.

75
00:07:26,054 --> 00:07:27,106
Hmm.

76
00:07:27,930 --> 00:07:28,640
Hmm.

77
00:07:43,831 --> 00:07:44,882
It's Foei.

78
00:07:45,725 --> 00:07:46,700
Oh.

79
00:07:50,198 --> 00:07:51,134
Hello.

80
00:07:51,364 --> 00:07:53,295
Wayu, where are you?

81
00:07:53,295 --> 00:07:55,015
You ignored my calls all night.

82
00:07:55,818 --> 00:08:00,272
I caused trouble.
I can resign if you want.

83
00:08:00,903 --> 00:08:03,541
Just because your boyfriend told you
to quit, you're quitting?

84
00:08:04,401 --> 00:08:09,486
Yes. I messed things up, and it's
happened more than once already.

85
00:08:09,773 --> 00:08:11,799
I've fixed the issue for you, Wayu.

86
00:08:11,818 --> 00:08:14,666
Just come to the sport day event first.
Then we'll talk.

87
00:08:15,985 --> 00:08:17,018
Alright.

88
00:08:23,823 --> 00:08:24,855
How are you doing?

89
00:08:27,723 --> 00:08:30,036
Foei told me to go to the bar's
sport day event.

90
00:08:31,909 --> 00:08:32,750
Today?

91
00:08:33,935 --> 00:08:34,853
Yeah.

92
00:08:38,045 --> 00:08:40,014
I'm scared they're going to fire me.

93
00:08:50,452 --> 00:08:52,956
It's okay. If they fire you,
they fire you.

94
00:08:53,721 --> 00:08:54,772
I'll take care of you.

95
00:08:55,785 --> 00:08:58,595
You can go back to school
and do what you really want.

96
00:09:04,139 --> 00:09:08,096
At first, I only planned to do this job
for a little while.

97
00:09:08,478 --> 00:09:11,498
I thought I'd save up
some money and then quit.

98
00:09:15,704 --> 00:09:18,036
But everyone's been so good to me.

99
00:09:18,036 --> 00:09:20,751
The people at the bar, and everyone
in the neighborhood too.

100
00:09:21,286 --> 00:09:24,497
They don't just feel like coworkers.
They've become family to me.

101
00:09:30,882 --> 00:09:33,061
So, are you planning to keep doing
this job forever?

102
00:09:34,667 --> 00:09:36,196
Probably not.

103
00:09:36,636 --> 00:09:38,682
But if you want me to quit completely,

104
00:09:39,026 --> 00:09:40,861
I don't think I can do that yet.

105
00:09:41,702 --> 00:09:44,627
When I was going through a hard time,

106
00:09:44,627 --> 00:09:49,291
it was only Foei, Tai, and the people
at the bar who were there supporting me.

107
00:09:52,044 --> 00:09:53,038
Okay.

108
00:09:54,471 --> 00:09:55,465
Then...

109
00:09:57,606 --> 00:09:59,231
I'll go to the sport day with you.

110
00:10:01,774 --> 00:10:05,138
But what if Foei scolds you
and throws you out?

111
00:10:05,616 --> 00:10:06,782
That's okay.

112
00:10:07,145 --> 00:10:09,458
At least I'll get to apologize
and explain myself.

113
00:10:10,816 --> 00:10:13,760
I caused you trouble, Wayu.
So I should take responsibility for it.

114
00:10:15,270 --> 00:10:18,768
Humph. Then you can spoil me
to your heart's content.

115
00:10:19,838 --> 00:10:22,572
You're this tiny.
I can handle you just fine.

116
00:10:25,115 --> 00:10:26,261
You sure?

117
00:10:33,621 --> 00:10:36,966
I eat a lot, and I'm great
at having fun.

118
00:10:38,515 --> 00:10:42,453
Of course. Whatever you want to do,
wherever you want to go,

119
00:10:42,453 --> 00:10:44,441
I'll take you there. Okay?

120
00:10:44,804 --> 00:10:48,073
Alright then, you have to take me out.

121
00:10:48,073 --> 00:10:51,227
Take me swimming, take me for good food,

122
00:10:51,227 --> 00:10:54,171
and shout that you love me
for the whole world to hear.

123
00:10:54,171 --> 00:10:55,738
Then we won't have this problem again.

124
00:10:57,574 --> 00:11:00,556
Of course, if you're not embarrassed.

125
00:11:00,556 --> 00:11:03,557
Humph. I know you won't actually do it.

126
00:11:14,950 --> 00:11:17,340
Come on! Stay strong.

127
00:11:17,340 --> 00:11:20,169
Energy!

128
00:11:20,169 --> 00:11:22,635
Sports! Sports! The ultimate cure!

129
00:11:22,635 --> 00:11:25,254
Ha-hi!

130
00:11:25,254 --> 00:11:27,242
Yeah, warm up well.

131
00:11:28,886 --> 00:11:30,071
Oh, no!

132
00:11:42,038 --> 00:11:44,179
Foei, please calm down.

133
00:11:44,179 --> 00:11:49,034
Let's talk this through. We're here
for the soccer match. Everyone's waiting.

134
00:11:49,034 --> 00:11:50,621
Easy, okay?

135
00:11:50,942 --> 00:11:52,369
Calm down.

136
00:11:54,941 --> 00:11:58,573
Wasn't causing trouble enough?
You've still got the nerve to show up here?

137
00:12:00,943 --> 00:12:02,090
I'm sorry.

138
00:12:02,434 --> 00:12:03,753
I really went too far.

139
00:12:05,146 --> 00:12:06,879
But this isn't Wayu's fault.

140
00:12:07,768 --> 00:12:09,316
Please let him keep working.

141
00:12:10,654 --> 00:12:11,572
Wait.

142
00:12:12,757 --> 00:12:15,720
I'll buy all of Wayu's drinks
for the whole month myself.

143
00:12:15,720 --> 00:12:17,478
That way the bar won't lose any money.

144
00:12:19,639 --> 00:12:21,723
You really serious about Wayu?

145
00:12:27,266 --> 00:12:29,369
I don't know what I can say
to make you believe me,

146
00:12:30,688 --> 00:12:34,225
but I'll show you just
how much I love him.

147
00:12:36,442 --> 00:12:37,876
Ow.

148
00:12:40,399 --> 00:12:41,240
Go.

149
00:12:42,406 --> 00:12:43,534
Get in position.

150
00:12:46,191 --> 00:12:49,536
From now on, don't let me see you
at the bar again.

151
00:12:49,613 --> 00:12:51,639
If I catch you there again,

152
00:12:51,639 --> 00:12:54,067
you're out.

153
00:12:56,858 --> 00:13:00,089
Everyone, gather
in the middle of the field.

154
00:13:00,089 --> 00:13:02,440
- Got it. Let's go.
- Come on.

155
00:13:02,440 --> 00:13:03,816
Red team, hurry up.

156
00:13:04,228 --> 00:13:06,228
Come on, strategize. Strategize.

157
00:13:06,760 --> 00:13:07,659
Got it.

158
00:13:08,194 --> 00:13:10,316
From now on, I won't be coming
to Moonlit anymore.

159
00:13:11,711 --> 00:13:12,552
And...

160
00:13:14,808 --> 00:13:15,726
Thank you.

161
00:13:17,236 --> 00:13:19,472
For not firing Wayu.

162
00:13:19,850 --> 00:13:22,308
And thank you
for looking after him all this time.

163
00:13:23,219 --> 00:13:26,144
Yeah, just don't lead him astray
until it costs him his job.

164
00:13:26,450 --> 00:13:28,629
From now on, take good care of him too.

165
00:13:37,212 --> 00:13:38,684
Ow.

166
00:13:40,615 --> 00:13:41,895
Foei.

167
00:13:42,431 --> 00:13:44,686
You're really not firing me, right?

168
00:13:45,432 --> 00:13:46,904
But docking your pay, not sure.

169
00:13:46,904 --> 00:13:49,262
Come on, Foei.

170
00:13:49,434 --> 00:13:52,562
I've barely had anything to drink lately.
Could you not deduct it?

171
00:13:52,562 --> 00:13:55,812
Oh, fine. No deductions.

172
00:13:56,290 --> 00:13:59,406
But seriously,
no more kissing in the bar.

173
00:13:59,406 --> 00:14:01,356
- Really?
- Yeah.

174
00:14:03,172 --> 00:14:05,160
- Love you the most.
- What is with you?

175
00:14:05,160 --> 00:14:07,568
- Get out.
- You're the best, Foei.

176
00:14:07,568 --> 00:14:09,786
- Ow!
- Go join your friends over there.

177
00:14:10,703 --> 00:14:11,812
Ow, go.

178
00:14:16,476 --> 00:14:20,719
- Hey! Come on! Come on!
- You're coming!

179
00:14:20,719 --> 00:14:23,186
Your head's not in it at all, huh?

180
00:14:26,780 --> 00:14:29,953
Team Sky! Team Sky! Hey!

181
00:14:29,953 --> 00:14:34,006
M-O-O-N-L-I-T, Moonlit, hey!

182
00:14:35,669 --> 00:14:39,377
- Go for it! We can do it this time.
- Babe.

183
00:14:39,377 --> 00:14:42,034
- Hello.
- Hey, babe.

184
00:14:42,264 --> 00:14:44,405
- Here.
- Why didn't you say you were coming?

185
00:14:44,405 --> 00:14:45,705
I brought you flowers. It's a surprise.

186
00:14:45,705 --> 00:14:46,928
Wow, thank you.

187
00:14:46,928 --> 00:14:50,121
(Moonlit Host Club Sport Day)
There's one more thing, a sport day gift.

188
00:14:50,140 --> 00:14:51,707
- Wow, already got a gift?
- Yep.

189
00:14:51,707 --> 00:14:55,397
Wow! The game hasn't even started yet,

190
00:14:55,397 --> 00:14:58,513
and you've already got flowers and gifts
right here on the sidelines?

191
00:14:58,513 --> 00:15:01,418
Hey, doesn't "babe" mean "pig"?

192
00:15:01,782 --> 00:15:03,674
Man, he even brought his girl here
just to show off.

193
00:15:04,706 --> 00:15:08,357
The second his girl shows up,
your partner looks plain in comparison.

194
00:15:08,357 --> 00:15:09,973
Why don't you get your man
to buy you something too?

195
00:15:09,973 --> 00:15:11,378
Nah, I'm good.

196
00:15:11,550 --> 00:15:14,570
My man isn't insane
like Sky's girlfriend.

197
00:15:14,570 --> 00:15:17,648
Just having him here
to cheer me on is enough.

198
00:15:23,325 --> 00:15:25,390
- Just take a close-up of my face.
- Hurry.

199
00:15:25,390 --> 00:15:26,632
- Yeah.
- Go.

200
00:15:31,756 --> 00:15:34,145
Rose, you're free right now, yeah?

201
00:15:34,929 --> 00:15:36,305
I've got something I need help with.

202
00:15:36,611 --> 00:15:40,396
Today, whichever team wins gets 100,000!

203
00:15:40,396 --> 00:15:43,378
- Yeah!
- Come on.

204
00:15:43,378 --> 00:15:45,309
Hey, it's not just about the money.

205
00:15:45,309 --> 00:15:46,797
But it's about pride.

206
00:15:46,800 --> 00:15:49,075
We must win, Team Sky!

207
00:15:49,075 --> 00:15:50,241
- Hey!
- Hey!

208
00:15:50,241 --> 00:15:53,682
Let's crush them all, especially Sky.

209
00:15:53,682 --> 00:15:55,631
- Yay!
- Wow!

210
00:15:55,631 --> 00:15:57,632
100,000 must be ours.

211
00:15:57,632 --> 00:15:59,008
- Yay!
- Hey!

212
00:15:59,008 --> 00:16:01,003
- Go for it!
- Go all out, guys!

213
00:16:01,003 --> 00:16:05,495
- Okay, everyone ready?
- Here we go.

214
00:16:06,853 --> 00:16:07,751
What is it?

215
00:16:10,198 --> 00:16:12,377
(Food Support)

216
00:16:12,377 --> 00:16:15,245
(Wayu and Friends)

217
00:16:18,170 --> 00:16:21,285
Wayu and friends. Darn!

218
00:16:21,285 --> 00:16:24,478
Your Officer is just as insane
as Sky's babe, right?

219
00:16:26,714 --> 00:16:28,358
What's this, Krit? Huh?

220
00:16:29,199 --> 00:16:30,060
Oh.

221
00:16:31,207 --> 00:16:32,373
For morale, you know.

222
00:16:35,374 --> 00:16:38,566
Did I do good?
I know how this works, right?

223
00:16:38,853 --> 00:16:42,370
I'm not just cheering for you.
I'm cheering for your friends too.

224
00:16:44,263 --> 00:16:47,302
What's this? Hmph.
Can't you ease up a little?

225
00:16:47,608 --> 00:16:49,520
You're spending way too much on this.

226
00:16:50,246 --> 00:16:51,298
Do you like it?

227
00:16:52,693 --> 00:16:55,121
Hey, Tai, We're on a different team
from Wayu. Can we join?

228
00:16:55,121 --> 00:16:56,077
- Sure.
- Really?

229
00:16:56,077 --> 00:16:57,854
- Hey, idiot.
- What now?

230
00:16:57,874 --> 00:17:01,219
If you want food, tell me. Why go to
another team? I'll order it for you.

231
00:17:01,219 --> 00:17:04,124
Foei, Wayu's pretty lucky too, huh?

232
00:17:04,124 --> 00:17:06,361
At this rate, forget the hundred grand.

233
00:17:13,893 --> 00:17:16,015
Go!

234
00:17:17,047 --> 00:17:18,806
Babe, keep it up, babe!

235
00:17:24,101 --> 00:17:25,898
It's okay. Try again, Wayu.

236
00:17:27,542 --> 00:17:30,294
Wayu, go, go!

237
00:17:30,294 --> 00:17:33,296
Team Sky.

238
00:17:35,016 --> 00:17:36,679
Hey.

239
00:17:41,745 --> 00:17:44,880
Red ties it, 1-1.

240
00:17:50,041 --> 00:17:54,132
- Shoot!
- Pass to Wayu!

241
00:17:55,031 --> 00:17:56,675
Hey.

242
00:17:59,790 --> 00:18:03,592
(Red Team 1 vs Blue Team 2)
Blue takes the lead, 2-1.

243
00:18:03,996 --> 00:18:04,799
Mwah!

244
00:18:07,227 --> 00:18:12,503
- Run!
- That's it!

245
00:18:12,503 --> 00:18:15,122
Wayu, come on!

246
00:18:19,463 --> 00:18:22,902
Red ties it again, 2-2.

247
00:18:22,902 --> 00:18:26,878
Wayu!

248
00:18:26,878 --> 00:18:29,248
- So close!
- Keep it up, babe!

249
00:18:29,306 --> 00:18:30,068
Nice! Pass it!

250
00:18:31,695 --> 00:18:35,557
- Whoa!
- It's okay!

251
00:18:35,557 --> 00:18:39,628
Red and Blue are tied, 2-2.

252
00:18:39,628 --> 00:18:41,521
Babe, how are you? Tired?

253
00:18:41,521 --> 00:18:42,744
Whoa, not tired at all.

254
00:18:42,744 --> 00:18:44,713
No worries, not tired.

255
00:18:45,574 --> 00:18:48,269
Keep it up!

256
00:18:54,252 --> 00:18:56,317
A hundred grand. Keep thinking
a hundred grand.

257
00:18:56,317 --> 00:18:58,936
- Ah!
- Uh-huh!

258
00:19:01,497 --> 00:19:04,021
Okay.

259
00:19:12,967 --> 00:19:18,606
Hey!

260
00:19:18,606 --> 00:19:19,963
Awesome!

261
00:19:19,963 --> 00:19:24,245
Tai, woo-hoo!

262
00:19:25,736 --> 00:19:26,654
Go, Richy!

263
00:19:28,833 --> 00:19:32,217
Oh! Go!

264
00:19:32,274 --> 00:19:34,664
- Block him. That's it!
- Go! Take it!

265
00:19:36,002 --> 00:19:40,838
Wayu!

266
00:19:41,526 --> 00:19:42,635
Wayu!

267
00:19:46,974 --> 00:19:48,504
Come on, Wayu!

268
00:19:59,228 --> 00:20:01,255
Wayu!

269
00:20:01,255 --> 00:20:04,523
(Moonlit Host Club Sport Day)
Red wins, earns a hundred thousand.

270
00:20:04,523 --> 00:20:07,696
- Yay!
- Thank you!

271
00:20:07,696 --> 00:20:09,933
That was amazing. So good!

272
00:20:09,933 --> 00:20:13,031
Come on, everyone! Let's take photos.

273
00:20:13,565 --> 00:20:14,750
Come.

274
00:20:15,304 --> 00:20:16,987
Come on. I'll take it for you.

275
00:20:21,747 --> 00:20:23,639
One, two, three.

276
00:20:24,977 --> 00:20:26,067
Change poses, please.

277
00:20:26,201 --> 00:20:28,227
Alright, switch it up!

278
00:20:28,227 --> 00:20:30,980
- Come on! Come on!
- Show us some Moonlit spirit!

279
00:20:31,209 --> 00:20:33,599
- Blue team, move to the center!
- Turn to the right.

280
00:20:33,599 --> 00:20:35,128
- Yeah.
- Come on.

281
00:20:35,128 --> 00:20:36,389
Look over here!

282
00:20:37,842 --> 00:20:39,601
One, two, three.

283
00:20:43,998 --> 00:20:46,693
Amazing. You guys did great.

284
00:20:46,693 --> 00:20:49,163
- Man, you're lucky.
- Awesome.

285
00:20:49,163 --> 00:20:49,981
Nice job.

286
00:20:53,345 --> 00:20:55,028
One, two, three.

287
00:20:55,028 --> 00:20:59,270
Wow, is this Poppy's car?

288
00:20:59,270 --> 00:21:02,846
We may've lost on the field,
but in real life, Sky wins hands down.

289
00:21:02,846 --> 00:21:05,235
Hey, why're you taking shots
at my friend?

290
00:21:05,235 --> 00:21:08,065
- Just curse directly.
- Hey, Tai, that's enough.

291
00:21:08,065 --> 00:21:10,837
Why ruin the mood
on a nice day like this?

292
00:21:11,620 --> 00:21:15,425
Come on, Richy. Let's go ride in style.

293
00:21:16,170 --> 00:21:18,253
Let's go eat something expensive.

294
00:21:18,636 --> 00:21:20,223
- Humph.
- Let's go.

295
00:21:25,499 --> 00:21:27,544
- Come on.
- Alright.

296
00:21:33,011 --> 00:21:34,024
See you.

297
00:21:37,733 --> 00:21:40,849
Ugh... Hey, what should we eat?

298
00:21:41,442 --> 00:21:43,621
Suki? I'm good with anything.

299
00:21:44,060 --> 00:21:46,890
Move. Please make way.

300
00:21:46,890 --> 00:21:48,591
I'll eat extra for you, alright?

301
00:21:51,458 --> 00:21:53,293
Tomorrow, I could drive a car
like this to pick you up.

302
00:21:54,249 --> 00:21:55,912
Are you crazy? No way.

303
00:21:56,180 --> 00:21:58,111
What kind of car do you want?
I can buy it for you.

304
00:21:58,589 --> 00:22:00,156
What? Do you have money to burn?

305
00:22:00,156 --> 00:22:01,934
You should save your money
for when you really need it.

306
00:22:01,934 --> 00:22:04,687
I can take a motorbike taxi
or the skytrain. It's really no problem.

307
00:22:05,375 --> 00:22:08,950
See, Captain? He's stingy as heck.

308
00:22:09,141 --> 00:22:11,473
What about you?
Are you coming to celebrate with us?

309
00:22:12,333 --> 00:22:13,767
Captain, want to come with us?

310
00:22:15,793 --> 00:22:18,412
Well, that's up to Wayu.

311
00:22:19,043 --> 00:22:22,007
In that case, I'm beat today.

312
00:22:23,478 --> 00:22:26,536
Alright, you guys go on ahead.
Take our friends to celebrate.

313
00:22:28,085 --> 00:22:32,519
- Bet you want to be with your man...
- Hey!

314
00:22:34,355 --> 00:22:36,993
The Captain, right?

315
00:22:39,115 --> 00:22:42,594
Alright then, I'm off to go be
lovey-dovey with my boyfriend.

316
00:22:42,995 --> 00:22:47,812
As for those whose partners don't care,
go hang with your friends.

317
00:22:48,348 --> 00:22:49,132
Go.

318
00:22:49,648 --> 00:22:50,909
Ouch, that stings.

319
00:22:50,909 --> 00:22:53,089
You really hit me where it hurts.

320
00:22:53,815 --> 00:22:55,630
Okay, I'm heading out then.

321
00:22:55,630 --> 00:22:57,791
- See you.
- Just go, what're you waiting for?

322
00:22:57,791 --> 00:22:59,186
Okay, I'm going.

323
00:22:59,186 --> 00:23:00,773
- Fine, I'm going.
- Heh, go on.

324
00:23:02,761 --> 00:23:03,908
- Go.
- Go.

325
00:23:09,433 --> 00:23:10,599
Hold out your hand.

326
00:23:12,358 --> 00:23:13,294
Why?

327
00:23:14,174 --> 00:23:15,149
Just do it.

328
00:23:17,328 --> 00:23:18,092
Here.

329
00:23:22,642 --> 00:23:24,859
Hey, what's this?

330
00:23:26,809 --> 00:23:27,956
It's a gift.

331
00:23:28,664 --> 00:23:31,474
You don't have anything from me
to keep with you.

332
00:23:31,913 --> 00:23:35,125
So when you miss me, you'll have
something to look at instead.

333
00:23:36,463 --> 00:23:40,267
Wow, you're this possessive?

334
00:23:40,267 --> 00:23:43,995
I think it's more like a reminder
that I already have a boyfriend.

335
00:23:46,289 --> 00:23:47,340
That's not wrong.

336
00:23:49,366 --> 00:23:50,819
Thank you.

337
00:23:51,546 --> 00:23:52,845
Come here, let me put it on for you.

338
00:23:57,070 --> 00:24:00,702
Oh, Krit, the bar's closed tomorrow
for its annual day off.

339
00:24:00,951 --> 00:24:02,729
Want to take a trip out of town?

340
00:24:02,862 --> 00:24:04,315
Do you have the day off too?

341
00:24:04,678 --> 00:24:07,240
Hmm, I'd have to check.

342
00:24:07,240 --> 00:24:09,457
But I've already assigned everything
to my team.

343
00:24:10,891 --> 00:24:14,313
Mm-hmm, in that case...

344
00:24:14,638 --> 00:24:17,773
It's okay if you can't. I just...

345
00:24:18,308 --> 00:24:19,837
want to go on a trip with you.

346
00:24:23,699 --> 00:24:25,763
Honestly, it depends on who's asking.

347
00:24:26,490 --> 00:24:30,714
If the one asking is cute,
I might take the day off.

348
00:24:33,238 --> 00:24:34,748
You're getting bold these days.

349
00:24:37,099 --> 00:24:38,399
In that case...

350
00:24:42,968 --> 00:24:44,535
Captain Krit, sir.

351
00:24:45,759 --> 00:24:48,320
Could you take Wayu on a trip, please?

352
00:24:53,902 --> 00:24:57,477
Hmm... Maybe I can make time.

353
00:24:58,643 --> 00:25:00,153
Krit...

354
00:25:01,224 --> 00:25:04,665
Could you please take Wayu on a trip?

355
00:25:06,079 --> 00:25:09,941
Pretty please? Wayu really wants
to go with Krit.

356
00:25:10,591 --> 00:25:12,770
Please?

357
00:25:12,770 --> 00:25:15,924
- Alright.
- Yay!

358
00:25:22,920 --> 00:25:25,769
So, where do you want to go, babe?
That way I'll know where to take you.

359
00:25:29,764 --> 00:25:33,683
"Babe," huh? That's actually
kind of cute.

360
00:25:33,683 --> 00:25:37,506
But could we switch to just
Krit and Wayu?

361
00:25:37,716 --> 00:25:39,819
I can't take it. It's too embarrassing.

362
00:25:41,367 --> 00:25:45,229
- So, where do you want to go, babe?
- Anywhere is fine. But not "babe".

363
00:25:45,229 --> 00:25:48,402
- Not that.
- Alright. Got it, babe.

364
00:25:48,402 --> 00:25:51,805
Don't call me "babe",
or I'm seriously going to get mad.

365
00:25:51,805 --> 00:25:53,353
Let me see you mad then, babe.

366
00:25:53,678 --> 00:25:55,972
Hey, I told you not to.

367
00:25:57,616 --> 00:26:00,311
Okay then, babe.

368
00:26:01,478 --> 00:26:04,766
If you call me "babe" again,
I'm not going on the trip with you.

369
00:26:04,766 --> 00:26:08,684
Whoa. Alright...

370
00:26:10,309 --> 00:26:11,513
Wow.

371
00:26:12,450 --> 00:26:14,171
That's really beautiful, Krit.

372
00:26:14,878 --> 00:26:15,815
Wow.

373
00:26:18,070 --> 00:26:19,963
Come on, let's take a picture first.

374
00:26:20,995 --> 00:26:22,944
- Here, selfie.
- Mm.

375
00:26:32,637 --> 00:26:33,401
Here.

376
00:26:34,625 --> 00:26:38,544
Out here like this, we don't have
to worry about clients seeing us, right?

377
00:26:41,679 --> 00:26:45,521
Exactly, and we can do this too.

378
00:26:47,261 --> 00:26:48,255
Hmm.

379
00:26:52,078 --> 00:26:54,257
Is there anywhere you'd like to go?

380
00:26:54,525 --> 00:26:57,029
Hmm, no idea at all.

381
00:26:57,430 --> 00:27:00,145
I've never been to Kanchanaburi before.
This is my first time.

382
00:27:01,903 --> 00:27:02,936
Alright then.

383
00:27:05,555 --> 00:27:06,656
(Songkurai Waterfall, Viewpoint)
I made a list, just in case.

384
00:27:07,104 --> 00:27:08,608
(Cycling, Boat ride to the sunken temple)
Take a look and see where you want to go.

385
00:27:08,823 --> 00:27:10,912
(Temple visit, Chic café, Mon Bridge, Bo Ong)
Wow.

386
00:27:11,552 --> 00:27:13,258
You really did your homework.

387
00:27:14,138 --> 00:27:14,922
(Songkurai Waterfall,
Viewpoint,)

388
00:27:14,941 --> 00:27:15,954
(Cycling, Boat trip to sunken temple)
That's a lot.

389
00:27:16,776 --> 00:27:19,299
(Temple visit, Chic cafes, Mon Bridge, Bo Ong)
This one's beautiful too, but...

390
00:27:19,815 --> 00:27:22,147
With this many places,
are we really going to all of them?

391
00:27:23,524 --> 00:27:24,575
Not all of them.

392
00:27:24,690 --> 00:27:27,251
But from the ones I listed,

393
00:27:28,150 --> 00:27:29,526
I thought you'd like these.

394
00:27:31,725 --> 00:27:33,216
You really get me.

395
00:27:48,642 --> 00:27:53,345
♪Awakened from the trance of emptiness♪

396
00:27:53,345 --> 00:27:57,837
♪There's no such thing
as loneliness anymore♪

397
00:27:57,837 --> 00:28:02,406
♪Since you came and changed the story♪

398
00:28:02,922 --> 00:28:06,841
♪This heart knows only longing for you♪

399
00:28:06,841 --> 00:28:11,448
♪To truly understand
a love beyond reason♪

400
00:28:11,601 --> 00:28:15,902
♪When I found someone like you♪

401
00:28:15,902 --> 00:28:20,490
♪My whole life no longer
has to keep dreaming♪

402
00:28:21,101 --> 00:28:24,657
♪Now that you're right here♪

403
00:28:24,657 --> 00:28:29,685
♪I love you with all my heart,
and I'm ready to give you everything♪

404
00:28:29,685 --> 00:28:34,559
♪All one life can offer♪

405
00:28:34,559 --> 00:28:39,616
♪I won't leave you behind,
no matter what I face♪

406
00:28:39,616 --> 00:28:42,989
♪No matter how bad♪

407
00:28:42,989 --> 00:28:47,883
♪I give you my all,
my body and everything♪

408
00:28:47,883 --> 00:28:52,662
♪Please trust your life
with someone like me♪

409
00:28:52,662 --> 00:28:56,992
♪I assure you there's no one♪

410
00:28:57,440 --> 00:29:03,022
♪Could ever love you more than I do♪

411
00:29:09,446 --> 00:29:11,186
- Krit.
- Hm.

412
00:29:12,103 --> 00:29:14,015
I'm going to run to the restroom first.

413
00:29:14,015 --> 00:29:16,270
- Let's go
- Okay, give me a sec.

414
00:29:17,589 --> 00:29:19,291
- I'll be waiting here.
- Okay.

415
00:29:22,980 --> 00:29:25,561
- No, I skip it.
- Thank you.

416
00:29:25,561 --> 00:29:26,650
Let's keep eating.

417
00:29:28,275 --> 00:29:29,977
Would you like a souvenir?

418
00:29:52,190 --> 00:29:55,286
Why? Is this outfit uncomfortable?

419
00:29:56,491 --> 00:29:58,995
Oh... No. It's just...

420
00:30:00,180 --> 00:30:02,340
I'm just not used to
colorful outfits like this.

421
00:30:03,449 --> 00:30:07,769
Come on, Krit, you look
really cute in this.

422
00:30:10,216 --> 00:30:12,682
I agreed to wear it

423
00:30:13,485 --> 00:30:14,919
because it's a matching set, you know?

424
00:30:16,352 --> 00:30:17,423
Thank you.

425
00:30:21,571 --> 00:30:22,584
Phew...

426
00:30:24,037 --> 00:30:27,994
I really wish I could bring Mom,
Wai, and Singto here too.

427
00:30:29,026 --> 00:30:30,594
I think they'd really like it.

428
00:30:35,277 --> 00:30:37,514
But right now, I still don't even know
where Wai is.

429
00:30:42,063 --> 00:30:42,943
Well...

430
00:30:45,849 --> 00:30:47,206
Have you heard from Wai at all?

431
00:30:51,335 --> 00:30:53,246
Ever since she ran away from home,

432
00:30:54,317 --> 00:30:56,075
she hasn't contacted us once.

433
00:30:57,452 --> 00:30:59,765
She's even blocked everyone
on social media.

434
00:31:02,938 --> 00:31:05,958
I feel so bad for Singto,
having to grow up like this.

435
00:31:06,800 --> 00:31:07,602
And...

436
00:31:09,017 --> 00:31:10,604
Have you ever tried looking for her?

437
00:31:15,115 --> 00:31:16,759
She's unbelievably stubborn.

438
00:31:18,097 --> 00:31:19,665
Honestly, I just hope

439
00:31:20,238 --> 00:31:24,367
once she grows up, she'll realize things
and come back to see me and Singto.

440
00:31:39,106 --> 00:31:40,042
It's okay.

441
00:31:46,695 --> 00:31:47,957
No matter what

442
00:31:48,606 --> 00:31:50,193
I'll always be here for you, Wayu.

443
00:31:57,744 --> 00:31:58,662
Oh.

444
00:31:59,808 --> 00:32:02,905
Sorry, I got carried away
with my family drama.

445
00:32:04,358 --> 00:32:07,780
Hey, Krit, what time are we heading
back to Bangkok?

446
00:32:09,233 --> 00:32:10,036
Not yet.

447
00:32:11,699 --> 00:32:13,304
There's one more place
I want to take you.

448
00:32:17,701 --> 00:32:19,211
Look over there. Isn't it beautiful?

449
00:32:19,747 --> 00:32:23,398
- Wow, a house like that would be nice.
- Hmm.

450
00:32:24,831 --> 00:32:27,852
So... why did you bring me here?

451
00:32:30,413 --> 00:32:33,300
Didn't you want me to shout that
I love you for the whole world to hear?

452
00:32:35,575 --> 00:32:36,779
Wait... Don't tell me...

453
00:32:38,729 --> 00:32:41,826
No way. I know you wouldn't actually do
something like that.

454
00:32:44,196 --> 00:32:45,286
Wait a sec.

455
00:33:12,622 --> 00:33:14,744
I love you, Wayu.

456
00:33:16,502 --> 00:33:18,318
I love you, Wayu.

457
00:33:19,675 --> 00:33:20,612
Huh?

458
00:33:21,319 --> 00:33:24,932
- Did you hear me?
- Nope.

459
00:33:30,036 --> 00:33:30,858
Sorry.

460
00:33:32,177 --> 00:33:33,038
Well.

461
00:33:33,955 --> 00:33:37,568
Could you please walk over to
that handsome, sharp-looking guy over there?

462
00:33:37,568 --> 00:33:39,996
Sure. What do you want me to do?

463
00:33:40,684 --> 00:33:42,137
Please tell him this for me...

464
00:34:01,865 --> 00:34:02,801
Excuse me.

465
00:34:03,413 --> 00:34:05,114
That guy asked me to tell you...

466
00:34:05,841 --> 00:34:09,588
Wayu is the reason
I wake up every morning.

467
00:34:12,799 --> 00:34:13,850
Thank you.

468
00:34:19,451 --> 00:34:20,579
Excuse me.

469
00:34:20,579 --> 00:34:21,669
- Yes?
- Sorry.

470
00:34:26,314 --> 00:34:28,742
- Kid.
- Wow.

471
00:34:28,742 --> 00:34:30,711
Could you tell that person
something for me?

472
00:34:32,317 --> 00:34:33,522
Thank you.

473
00:34:40,517 --> 00:34:43,557
Wayu is my smile
and the light in my life.

474
00:34:44,226 --> 00:34:45,296
Thank you.

475
00:34:47,915 --> 00:34:51,222
Wayu is the one
who made my goals in life clearer.

476
00:34:51,911 --> 00:34:53,038
Thank you.

477
00:34:57,263 --> 00:34:58,353
Yeah.

478
00:34:58,353 --> 00:35:01,563
Thank you for coming into my life.

479
00:35:01,563 --> 00:35:03,438
Thank you.

480
00:35:29,072 --> 00:35:30,238
I love you, Wayu.

481
00:35:32,609 --> 00:35:33,870
That's cheating.

482
00:35:35,304 --> 00:35:37,311
First you surprised me with this trip,

483
00:35:37,311 --> 00:35:39,529
and then you did something
like that too.

484
00:35:41,632 --> 00:35:44,939
How is that cheating?
I did everything you asked.

485
00:35:46,162 --> 00:35:48,074
It's just you've done so much for me.

486
00:35:49,354 --> 00:35:51,897
But I don't have anything to give you.

487
00:35:56,638 --> 00:35:57,498
Mm.

488
00:36:02,621 --> 00:36:04,896
Even if it doesn't look like much,

489
00:36:05,680 --> 00:36:08,107
because you won't let me buy you
anything expensive,

490
00:36:08,929 --> 00:36:12,504
I still wanted to give you something.

491
00:36:24,719 --> 00:36:25,732
Thank you.

492
00:36:25,924 --> 00:36:30,894
♪I love you with all my heart,
and I'm ready to give you everything♪

493
00:36:30,894 --> 00:36:35,768
♪All one life can offer♪

494
00:36:35,768 --> 00:36:40,736
♪I won't leave you behind,
no matter what I face♪

495
00:36:40,736 --> 00:36:43,911
♪No matter how bad♪

496
00:36:44,179 --> 00:36:48,901
♪I give you my all,
my body and everything♪

497
00:36:48,920 --> 00:36:53,394
♪Please trust your life
with someone like me♪

498
00:36:53,833 --> 00:36:58,304
♪I assure you there's no one♪

499
00:36:58,304 --> 00:37:04,137
♪Could ever love you more than I do♪

500
00:37:05,150 --> 00:37:12,146
♪No one could ever
love you more than I do♪

501
00:37:14,631 --> 00:37:15,740
Mom, is it spicy today?

502
00:37:16,122 --> 00:37:19,410
- Oh, not spicy at all.
- Mm.

503
00:37:19,410 --> 00:37:21,666
Oh, Krit, you're back just in time.

504
00:37:21,934 --> 00:37:23,903
Come on, sit down and eat first.

505
00:37:24,610 --> 00:37:25,489
- Mm.
- Come on.

506
00:37:27,305 --> 00:37:27,993
Hmm?

507
00:37:35,506 --> 00:37:36,347
Hm?

508
00:37:37,303 --> 00:37:40,362
If I hadn't called you home, you probably
wouldn't have come back, huh?

509
00:37:40,801 --> 00:37:44,127
Why? Has Rose been staying over
at your condo a lot lately?

510
00:37:44,395 --> 00:37:46,421
That's why you never come home anymore?

511
00:37:46,421 --> 00:37:50,780
If that's how it is, I think you two
should just get married already.

512
00:37:51,812 --> 00:37:52,653
What do you think?

513
00:37:53,781 --> 00:37:56,400
Uh, well...

514
00:37:58,044 --> 00:37:58,694
Hey.

515
00:37:59,764 --> 00:38:02,403
You're practically living
together already,

516
00:38:02,403 --> 00:38:05,098
so make it official, will you?

517
00:38:09,418 --> 00:38:11,865
I think marriage is something
between two people.

518
00:38:12,132 --> 00:38:14,426
It's not my decision alone.

519
00:38:15,765 --> 00:38:18,880
Then ask Rose, dear.

520
00:38:18,880 --> 00:38:22,455
Whenever I ask her, she always
dodges the question.

521
00:38:23,029 --> 00:38:27,903
If that's the case, Dad and I
should talk to her parents.

522
00:38:27,903 --> 00:38:30,331
- Mm, I think that's a good idea.
- Mm.

523
00:38:30,694 --> 00:38:34,288
Alright, I'll try talking to her first.

524
00:38:34,288 --> 00:38:35,244
Then I'll let you know.

525
00:38:37,060 --> 00:38:40,883
I want you to marry Rose soon.

526
00:38:41,189 --> 00:38:43,636
You two have been together
a long time already.

527
00:38:43,655 --> 00:38:47,230
The longer you wait, the older you get.
Having kids will be harder.

528
00:38:51,531 --> 00:38:52,831
- Okay.
- Mm.

529
00:38:53,576 --> 00:38:56,023
We can talk later. Eat first, dear.

530
00:38:56,845 --> 00:38:58,240
- Here.
- Eat up.

531
00:39:15,292 --> 00:39:17,127
(Wayu)
(Have you made it home yet, Krit?)

532
00:39:23,550 --> 00:39:24,831
(Krit)
(Yes, I'm home.)

533
00:39:49,605 --> 00:39:51,155
(New post)
(It's the most precious ring,)

534
00:39:51,155 --> 00:39:52,585
(because the person
who gave it to me is the most precious)

535
00:39:53,120 --> 00:39:57,328
(and important person
in my life. Love you.)

536
00:40:05,988 --> 00:40:08,528
(Rose)
(Krit, your parents are planning)

537
00:40:08,528 --> 00:40:11,073
(to come to my house.
What should we do?)

538
00:40:24,836 --> 00:40:26,117
(Chainphop Udomdirek)

539
00:40:26,136 --> 00:40:28,525
Why so many questions?
I've already told you.

540
00:40:29,233 --> 00:40:31,030
I couldn't stand the sight of him,
so I killed him.

541
00:40:33,649 --> 00:40:36,516
You took the knife from the workshop
and planned it.

542
00:40:38,007 --> 00:40:39,613
It wasn't a crime of passion
anymore, was it?

543
00:40:40,569 --> 00:40:44,526
If you hated his guts enough
to plan it out, that's pretty calm.

544
00:40:46,170 --> 00:40:48,751
Well, he kept staring at me.

545
00:40:48,903 --> 00:40:51,197
It pissed me off, got it?

546
00:40:53,109 --> 00:40:56,053
I'm looking at you right now.
You want to kill me too?

547
00:41:00,086 --> 00:41:03,355
Maybe. If you don't stop
asking questions.

548
00:41:09,491 --> 00:41:10,810
That's a nice ring.

549
00:41:12,474 --> 00:41:15,322
It doesn't really suit you, Officer.
Did your lover give it to you?

550
00:41:16,851 --> 00:41:19,011
I'd really like to meet your lover.

551
00:41:19,547 --> 00:41:23,886
- I wonder if he's as inquisitive as you.
- None of your darn business.

552
00:41:27,136 --> 00:41:28,072
Sigh...

553
00:41:29,468 --> 00:41:32,507
How many times do I have to say it?
I killed him myself.

554
00:41:36,636 --> 00:41:40,173
Premeditated murder
carries the death penalty.

555
00:41:41,874 --> 00:41:46,437
You want to die when you'd be
out of jail in a few years? Huh?

556
00:41:47,188 --> 00:41:48,832
I'm asking you one last time.

557
00:41:49,673 --> 00:41:51,012
Who hired you?

558
00:41:57,186 --> 00:41:59,881
I did it myself.

559
00:41:59,881 --> 00:42:00,856
You beast.

560
00:42:01,430 --> 00:42:02,711
Officer, calm down.

561
00:42:02,711 --> 00:42:05,310
Officer, calm down. Please, Officer.

562
00:42:05,310 --> 00:42:06,974
- Haha.
- Lieutenant, get him out of here.

563
00:42:06,974 --> 00:42:08,101
- Haha.
- You...

564
00:42:08,101 --> 00:42:09,420
- Haha.
- Leave.

565
00:42:09,420 --> 00:42:12,078
Haha.

566
00:42:21,005 --> 00:42:22,477
- Could you take a photo?
- Let's take a picture.

567
00:42:22,477 --> 00:42:24,809
- Just some quick photos, okay?
- Sure, of course.

568
00:42:25,287 --> 00:42:28,116
- Look this way, please.
- Nice.

569
00:42:28,116 --> 00:42:30,372
- This way too.
- Okay.

570
00:42:31,805 --> 00:42:34,023
- So nice.
- Thanks so much.

571
00:42:34,023 --> 00:42:35,551
- Okay.
- Yes.

572
00:42:35,551 --> 00:42:37,276
I'd also like to sincerely
thank you, Por,

573
00:42:37,276 --> 00:42:40,159
for recognizing the seriousness
of the drug problem.

574
00:42:40,541 --> 00:42:41,823
And I'd also like to thank you

575
00:42:41,823 --> 00:42:46,811
for supporting the crackdown
on transnational drug trafficking rings.

576
00:42:47,767 --> 00:42:50,348
No, I'm the one who should be
thanking you, Mr. Pitak.

577
00:42:50,348 --> 00:42:53,903
For giving me the chance
to do some good for society.

578
00:42:53,903 --> 00:42:57,995
I grew up surrounded by drugs,

579
00:42:58,186 --> 00:43:01,569
so I know firsthand
just how destructive they can be.

580
00:43:02,391 --> 00:43:04,054
- We all have to work together.
- Yes, sir.

581
00:43:05,526 --> 00:43:08,011
- May we take more photos?
- Ah, sure.

582
00:43:08,011 --> 00:43:09,177
A little closer together, please.

583
00:43:09,177 --> 00:43:12,083
- One, two, three. Over here.
- Nice.

584
00:43:12,083 --> 00:43:13,459
- Yes.
- Great.

585
00:43:14,453 --> 00:43:16,587
- Great.
- Thank you.

586
00:43:16,587 --> 00:43:18,315
- So nice.
- Come, Krit.

587
00:43:21,526 --> 00:43:24,088
Por, this is my only son.

588
00:43:24,088 --> 00:43:25,923
Captain Kritsadawut.

589
00:43:25,923 --> 00:43:29,345
Ah, hello, Captain Krit.

590
00:43:32,747 --> 00:43:35,825
Sir, the Minister
is on the line for you.

591
00:43:36,972 --> 00:43:38,329
Then please excuse me.

592
00:43:38,673 --> 00:43:40,298
Of course, sir.

593
00:43:46,262 --> 00:43:48,958
I see that the ambitious youth
these days

594
00:43:49,168 --> 00:43:50,544
love to prove themselves.

595
00:43:52,418 --> 00:43:53,775
But if you ask me,

596
00:43:53,775 --> 00:43:58,067
following the beaten path is much safer.

597
00:44:00,255 --> 00:44:02,682
If you don't want to live
in your dad's shadow,

598
00:44:03,658 --> 00:44:06,220
you'd better learn how to stay in line.

599
00:44:08,418 --> 00:44:12,758
Haha.

600
00:44:13,331 --> 00:44:14,459
Por, may I interview you?

601
00:44:14,459 --> 00:44:15,720
Oh, certainly.

602
00:44:15,720 --> 00:44:17,192
What do you think of this project?

603
00:44:17,192 --> 00:44:19,964
Oh, I think it's a worthwhile project.

604
00:44:19,983 --> 00:44:20,767
(Wichai Rotchana-ampan or Por, 55,
Suspect linked to Supanut)

605
00:44:23,023 --> 00:44:23,864
Well...

606
00:44:30,459 --> 00:44:31,816
How'd it go? What have we got?

607
00:44:32,409 --> 00:44:34,225
As for Supanut and Por,

608
00:44:34,225 --> 00:44:36,576
we found nothing linking them
to the human trafficking case.

609
00:44:37,302 --> 00:44:38,621
Just great!

610
00:44:40,858 --> 00:44:42,712
And what about Por's birthday party?

611
00:44:42,942 --> 00:44:45,847
How's that going?
Did we get someone in yet?

612
00:44:46,478 --> 00:44:49,725
No one's made it in yet.
Their screening is extremely tight.

613
00:44:49,725 --> 00:44:51,582
This one's going to be tough, Captain.

614
00:44:55,635 --> 00:44:58,043
Then keep an eye on Por and Supanut.

615
00:44:58,846 --> 00:45:00,548
And then report to me.

616
00:45:01,542 --> 00:45:03,836
Let me know where they are
and what they're doing.

617
00:45:04,256 --> 00:45:05,556
And who they've met.

618
00:45:06,263 --> 00:45:07,066
Yes, sir.

619
00:45:10,330 --> 00:45:16,666
(Industrial Plastic Parts, D5)

620
00:45:26,139 --> 00:45:31,664
(Movement of Goods at Chainphop's Warehouse:
Industrial Plastic Parts, D5)

621
00:45:59,196 --> 00:46:05,006
(RTP Database Login, Username, Password)

622
00:46:05,006 --> 00:46:08,409
(Authenticating)

623
00:46:11,034 --> 00:46:14,042
(Missing Persons and Unidentified Remains
Information Management Service Center)

624
00:46:21,657 --> 00:46:23,550
- Hey, wait up, Sky.
- Yeah?

625
00:46:23,550 --> 00:46:26,360
This guy just booked you
four thousand drinks.

626
00:46:26,360 --> 00:46:28,233
Whoa, four thousand drinks.

627
00:46:28,233 --> 00:46:30,947
Yep, four thousand drinks.
Come on, I'll take you there.

628
00:46:33,356 --> 00:46:36,300
Hello, Sky is here now.

629
00:46:36,300 --> 00:46:37,466
Hello.

630
00:46:38,632 --> 00:46:41,461
Alright then, I'll have Sky
take care of you today.

631
00:46:45,476 --> 00:46:46,623
Hello.

632
00:46:47,254 --> 00:46:49,949
Is this your first time at the bar?

633
00:46:53,237 --> 00:46:55,531
So, what kind of company
do you want from me today?

634
00:46:56,104 --> 00:46:58,417
Want me to focus on drinking with you,

635
00:46:58,876 --> 00:47:01,438
or do you want a friendship vibe,

636
00:47:03,789 --> 00:47:06,962
or maybe more of a boyfriend vibe?

637
00:47:08,606 --> 00:47:10,652
Hehe. Well then...

638
00:47:10,766 --> 00:47:13,615
What exactly comes
with the boyfriend vibe?

639
00:47:13,959 --> 00:47:16,329
Well...

640
00:47:17,533 --> 00:47:21,854
That depends on how you want me
to look after you.

641
00:47:23,708 --> 00:47:25,906
And when Poppy comes here,

642
00:47:26,365 --> 00:47:30,819
and she asks for a boyfriend vibe,
what do you two actually do, huh?

643
00:47:32,195 --> 00:47:34,413
You spoil her.

644
00:47:35,120 --> 00:47:36,974
And hook up.

645
00:47:37,758 --> 00:47:39,440
Then you become a couple.

646
00:47:40,167 --> 00:47:43,474
Am I wrong? Huh?

647
00:47:46,131 --> 00:47:47,603
What do you mean by that?

648
00:47:49,323 --> 00:47:50,604
What do I mean?

649
00:47:51,464 --> 00:47:54,676
- You beast.
- Hey, what is it?

650
00:47:54,676 --> 00:47:57,582
I may be a host, but you should
show people some darn respect.

651
00:47:57,582 --> 00:48:00,678
Respect what!

652
00:48:00,678 --> 00:48:04,007
Should I respect someone
who's having an affair with my wife?

653
00:48:04,007 --> 00:48:06,604
What are you talking about?

654
00:48:06,604 --> 00:48:09,968
What's with the way
you're talking to me?

655
00:48:09,968 --> 00:48:12,205
- Yeah.
- Wow, you really are a piece of work.

656
00:48:12,205 --> 00:48:14,270
Huh? Don't tell me this wasn't you.

657
00:48:15,665 --> 00:48:18,896
Huh? Messing around with
someone else's wife, you bad guy.

658
00:48:18,896 --> 00:48:20,464
Darn it, you bad guy.

659
00:48:20,464 --> 00:48:21,744
What is this?

660
00:48:21,744 --> 00:48:25,606
And all the money she bled out of me,
she spent it on guys like you.

661
00:48:25,606 --> 00:48:27,766
On worthless parasites like you.

662
00:48:27,766 --> 00:48:30,442
The lot of you deserve
to be exposed. Go die.

663
00:48:30,442 --> 00:48:32,526
You vile monsters!

664
00:48:32,526 --> 00:48:34,208
What are you doing?

665
00:48:34,208 --> 00:48:35,948
May I see your watch, bro?

666
00:48:35,948 --> 00:48:38,624
- Don't touch me.
- That's a really nice watch, bro.

667
00:48:38,624 --> 00:48:40,841
Stop! Ouch, hey!

668
00:48:40,841 --> 00:48:43,586
Wow, that watch is gorgeous, bro.

669
00:48:43,586 --> 00:48:46,232
- Hey, my phone!
- Watch.

670
00:48:46,232 --> 00:48:47,111
Give it back.

671
00:48:49,080 --> 00:48:51,642
Ouch, what is going on?

672
00:48:51,642 --> 00:48:53,955
- I'm sorry.
- Apologies, sir.

673
00:48:53,955 --> 00:48:56,039
Sir, you've had too much to drink.

674
00:48:56,039 --> 00:48:59,499
I'm going to have to ask you to leave.

675
00:48:59,919 --> 00:49:03,398
Hey, your staff broke my stuff.

676
00:49:03,398 --> 00:49:06,532
And this monster stole my wife.

677
00:49:06,532 --> 00:49:09,458
What is wrong with
your customer service?

678
00:49:09,458 --> 00:49:10,490
I'm sorry, sir.

679
00:49:10,490 --> 00:49:13,797
As the manager, I can't interfere in

680
00:49:13,797 --> 00:49:15,250
a customer's personal relationship.

681
00:49:15,250 --> 00:49:17,601
- Whoa.
- And about what you just said,

682
00:49:17,601 --> 00:49:19,016
do you have any evidence of that?

683
00:49:19,016 --> 00:49:21,157
You idiot, the evidence's right here...

684
00:49:22,438 --> 00:49:23,642
Darn it, another loss.

685
00:49:25,248 --> 00:49:26,108
Darn.

686
00:49:27,542 --> 00:49:29,339
This is all your fault.

687
00:49:30,390 --> 00:49:32,168
Hey, are you all in on this
together or what?

688
00:49:32,512 --> 00:49:33,219
Hey.

689
00:49:33,602 --> 00:49:37,425
Since there's no evidence,
we can't draw any conclusions.

690
00:49:37,922 --> 00:49:41,669
As for the phone,
the bar will cover the repair costs.

691
00:49:41,669 --> 00:49:42,988
Or we'll buy you a new one.

692
00:49:45,454 --> 00:49:47,384
I can buy this piece of junk myself.

693
00:49:47,384 --> 00:49:50,022
Darn it, and you...

694
00:49:50,022 --> 00:49:52,641
Don't let me see your face again.

695
00:49:53,482 --> 00:49:56,216
If I run into you outside,

696
00:49:57,497 --> 00:49:59,007
I'll end you.

697
00:49:59,523 --> 00:50:01,416
Remember that.

698
00:50:02,773 --> 00:50:06,864
And as for you, keep running
the bar properly.

699
00:50:09,483 --> 00:50:10,916
Back off, you monster.

700
00:50:13,172 --> 00:50:14,567
Darn it.

701
00:50:22,405 --> 00:50:26,897
It's nothing, everyone.
Please enjoy the party.

702
00:50:26,897 --> 00:50:29,707
Have fun, enjoy!

703
00:50:29,707 --> 00:50:31,906
- Foei, we're heading back now, bye!
- Goodbye!

704
00:50:31,906 --> 00:50:33,569
- Get home safe.
- See you.

705
00:50:35,117 --> 00:50:37,621
- Here's the owner of the bar.
- Hmm.

706
00:50:38,673 --> 00:50:39,705
Foei.

707
00:50:40,737 --> 00:50:44,197
Thank you so much for helping me.

708
00:50:45,191 --> 00:50:46,663
You don't need to thank me.

709
00:50:47,160 --> 00:50:49,282
The person you should thank is...

710
00:50:51,251 --> 00:50:53,698
There, it's Wayu.

711
00:50:54,673 --> 00:50:56,929
If it weren't for him,
the situation would be worse.

712
00:50:58,133 --> 00:50:59,108
Yes?

713
00:51:02,281 --> 00:51:04,919
Wayu. I...

714
00:51:06,812 --> 00:51:09,469
Thank you so much for helping me.

715
00:51:12,604 --> 00:51:13,407
Heh.

716
00:51:14,248 --> 00:51:17,135
I didn't expect to hear that from you.

717
00:51:17,135 --> 00:51:17,880
Wait a minute.

718
00:51:18,606 --> 00:51:21,569
I'm apologizing to Wayu, not to you.

719
00:51:22,315 --> 00:51:23,079
Yeah.

720
00:51:23,901 --> 00:51:25,106
But honestly,

721
00:51:25,220 --> 00:51:28,527
I really am sorry to both of you.

722
00:51:28,527 --> 00:51:29,751
For everything that...

723
00:51:31,815 --> 00:51:34,090
For treating you both so badly.

724
00:51:36,939 --> 00:51:37,933
It's okay.

725
00:51:38,927 --> 00:51:41,774
I'm not really the type
to hold a grudge anyway.

726
00:51:41,774 --> 00:51:44,451
But please don't let it happen again.

727
00:51:47,701 --> 00:51:49,651
Agreed.

728
00:51:50,186 --> 00:51:51,734
Just like Wayu said.

729
00:51:51,868 --> 00:51:53,378
That's how soft-hearted people are.

730
00:51:54,181 --> 00:51:55,653
Mm.

731
00:51:56,418 --> 00:51:59,266
I'm really glad you two finally made up.

732
00:51:59,266 --> 00:52:02,554
- Aw, I'm going to cry.
- Seriously.

733
00:52:03,223 --> 00:52:04,695
But honestly, Foei,

734
00:52:05,594 --> 00:52:08,442
when something like this happens,

735
00:52:08,442 --> 00:52:11,328
it's made a lot of things
clearer for me.

736
00:52:14,769 --> 00:52:16,968
There's something
I want to tell you too, Foei.

737
00:52:17,426 --> 00:52:19,759
What is it? Is it serious?

738
00:52:24,213 --> 00:52:25,532
I'll just say it here.

739
00:52:29,259 --> 00:52:30,368
Sigh...

740
00:52:30,674 --> 00:52:32,681
I think I'm going to quit,

741
00:52:32,681 --> 00:52:34,382
and go work in Hong Kong, China.

742
00:52:34,382 --> 00:52:37,365
Whoa, why so sudden?

743
00:52:37,365 --> 00:52:40,672
I've wanted to go for a long time now.

744
00:52:41,608 --> 00:52:42,908
It's just that...

745
00:52:42,908 --> 00:52:45,240
My girlfriend, Poppy,
she's so good to me,

746
00:52:45,240 --> 00:52:47,553
so I couldn't bring myself
to leave this life behind.

747
00:52:47,553 --> 00:52:49,714
But after something like this happened,

748
00:52:49,714 --> 00:52:52,218
it makes it easier for me
to make decisions.

749
00:52:53,193 --> 00:52:57,150
Sky, you're really on a roll right now.

750
00:52:57,188 --> 00:52:59,769
Can't you wait a little longer
before leaving?

751
00:52:59,769 --> 00:53:01,700
Come on, this is exactly
when I need to go.

752
00:53:01,700 --> 00:53:03,477
While things are going well for me.

753
00:53:04,720 --> 00:53:08,447
You know, I've already checked
Hong Kong, China, out.

754
00:53:08,696 --> 00:53:10,646
If I go work over there,

755
00:53:10,646 --> 00:53:13,150
oh, I could make a ton of money, Foei.

756
00:53:13,876 --> 00:53:17,432
Besides, I don't really want to

757
00:53:17,852 --> 00:53:19,860
do this job for the rest of my life.

758
00:53:20,433 --> 00:53:21,580
You get that, right?

759
00:53:23,797 --> 00:53:25,078
Come on, Foei.

760
00:53:26,072 --> 00:53:29,016
If someone wants to chase their dream,
don't hold them back.

761
00:53:32,763 --> 00:53:34,025
Sky.

762
00:53:34,942 --> 00:53:39,970
I just hope Hong Kong, China,
is kind to you.

763
00:53:40,524 --> 00:53:45,227
And I hope you make
your dream come true.

764
00:53:46,125 --> 00:53:49,107
Sky, if it doesn't work out,

765
00:53:49,356 --> 00:53:50,694
you can always come back to Moonlit.

766
00:53:51,172 --> 00:53:55,932
I'll hold onto the No. 1 host seat
for you myself.

767
00:53:55,932 --> 00:53:58,417
- You've never been No. 1.
- Haha.

768
00:53:58,417 --> 00:53:59,946
- Oh, Foei.
- Come on!

769
00:53:59,946 --> 00:54:02,030
Darn, if Sky's leaving,

770
00:54:02,049 --> 00:54:06,503
I deserve a shot at the title.
Come on, respect my muscles.

771
00:54:06,503 --> 00:54:08,606
You should respect my muscles, too.

772
00:54:08,606 --> 00:54:10,517
Oh, my!

773
00:54:10,517 --> 00:54:14,417
- Close it up.
- Oh, my!

774
00:54:15,373 --> 00:54:16,309
Yeah.

775
00:54:16,787 --> 00:54:20,056
If things go well, just come back
and celebrate here.

776
00:54:21,050 --> 00:54:22,159
Good luck to you.

777
00:54:23,612 --> 00:54:25,199
Ow.

778
00:54:25,734 --> 00:54:29,136
- Love you the most.
- Don't forget me.

779
00:54:29,136 --> 00:54:32,099
Hey, Richy, who's going
to yell at you now, huh?

780
00:54:32,099 --> 00:54:33,513
- No one.
- Uh-huh.

781
00:54:33,513 --> 00:54:34,890
I could call to yell at you.

782
00:54:34,890 --> 00:54:35,636
Haha.

783
00:54:35,636 --> 00:54:37,566
- Come here.
- Give me a hug.

784
00:54:37,566 --> 00:54:40,644
Ow.

785
00:54:40,644 --> 00:54:42,384
Good luck.

786
00:54:42,384 --> 00:54:45,232
- Sky.
- I'll come back to visit.

787
00:54:45,232 --> 00:54:46,073
Uh-huh.

788
00:54:46,360 --> 00:54:48,138
Anyway, I wish you the best.

789
00:54:48,138 --> 00:54:49,820
(Monthly Anniversary)
Do you think the internet doesn't exist?

790
00:54:49,820 --> 00:54:51,349
You're acting like I'm about to die.

791
00:54:51,349 --> 00:54:54,542
Just send us some pictures too.
We want to see them.

792
00:54:54,542 --> 00:54:56,300
Hey, you ask
like we don't know each other.

793
00:55:11,631 --> 00:55:14,613
(You made me smile on a bad day.)

794
00:55:19,316 --> 00:55:22,107
(So shy. Someone took
a sneaky photo of me.)

795
00:55:23,923 --> 00:55:27,326
(Giving shoes to walk together forever.)

796
00:55:30,461 --> 00:55:32,583
(My boyfriend is so cute.)

797
00:55:39,789 --> 00:55:42,083
Oh. Heh.

798
00:55:46,231 --> 00:55:48,736
Happy one-month anniversary, Krit.

799
00:55:51,947 --> 00:55:53,935
How did you even find time
to do all this?

800
00:55:54,834 --> 00:55:58,963
If it makes you happy,
I'll always make time for it.

801
00:56:01,830 --> 00:56:02,939
I love you, Krit.

802
00:56:06,208 --> 00:56:07,393
Love you too, Wayu.

803
00:56:13,147 --> 00:56:15,728
Can I kiss the sunflower?

804
00:56:16,205 --> 00:56:17,123
Sure.

805
00:56:25,286 --> 00:56:26,299
Oh, right.

806
00:56:27,599 --> 00:56:28,975
I've got a gift for you too.

807
00:56:29,988 --> 00:56:31,173
What is it?

808
00:56:31,823 --> 00:56:35,341
I don't want anything expensive.
You've already given me so much.

809
00:56:35,570 --> 00:56:38,552
It's not expensive, but I'm telling you

810
00:56:39,298 --> 00:56:40,750
that you're definitely going to love it.

811
00:57:06,041 --> 00:57:09,023
Krit, why did you bring me here?

812
00:57:10,839 --> 00:57:12,139
Go inside and you'll see.

813
00:57:33,090 --> 00:57:34,065
Wai.

814
00:57:43,354 --> 00:57:45,038
(Missing Persons and Unidentified Remains
Information Management Service Center)

815
00:57:45,038 --> 00:57:47,982
Please help me find someone.
Her name is Waralak Tangsamai.

816
00:57:49,626 --> 00:57:50,868
I want to know where she is.

817
00:57:56,584 --> 00:57:58,572
I brought you here to take her home.

818
00:57:59,432 --> 00:58:01,210
Actually, I spoke to Wai already.

819
00:58:01,956 --> 00:58:03,275
She herself wants to go back.

820
00:58:04,766 --> 00:58:05,721
What about you, Wayu?

821
00:58:07,174 --> 00:58:08,723
Do you want to bring her home with you?

822
00:58:14,075 --> 00:58:16,388
If you don't want me
to come back, that's okay.

823
00:58:19,447 --> 00:58:23,423
I left everyone behind,
even my own child.

824
00:58:25,392 --> 00:58:28,220
I even made you drop
out of college because of me.

825
00:58:29,234 --> 00:58:31,299
Being hated wouldn't be surprising.

826
00:58:38,907 --> 00:58:41,660
Singto's old enough to notice
that his friends all have mothers.

827
00:58:43,648 --> 00:58:45,426
In a family where it's just the father,

828
00:58:47,299 --> 00:58:48,733
how would that make a child feel?

829
00:58:51,313 --> 00:58:52,174
But...

830
00:58:53,703 --> 00:58:56,111
You raised Singto better than I could.

831
00:58:58,405 --> 00:58:59,839
That's one thing.

832
00:59:01,483 --> 00:59:02,496
But there's something else.

833
00:59:08,250 --> 00:59:09,971
I want my sister back.

834
00:59:16,030 --> 00:59:18,458
I'm so angry with you, Wai.
Do you know that?

835
00:59:20,312 --> 00:59:23,295
But I'll forgive you if you come back
and live with us.

836
00:59:27,863 --> 00:59:29,890
Family should be together, you know?

837
00:59:42,296 --> 00:59:45,068
I'm sorry for being such a coward.

838
00:59:47,668 --> 00:59:50,076
Anyway, I'm sorry.

839
00:59:50,955 --> 00:59:54,637
For disappointing you
right up to the very end.

840
01:00:00,514 --> 01:00:02,272
I'm not disappointed in you at all.

841
01:00:02,272 --> 01:00:04,241
Hmm, come here.

842
01:00:08,428 --> 01:00:11,849
That's enough. Don't cry.

843
01:00:15,290 --> 01:00:16,456
Let's stay together.

844
01:00:21,082 --> 01:00:22,879
Thank you.

845
01:00:29,742 --> 01:00:32,571
Your dad's totally disappeared lately.

846
01:00:32,571 --> 01:00:35,553
Hm? He never comes by to help.

847
01:00:36,203 --> 01:00:39,434
Good thing he sends money. Otherwise,
you'd be living on rice and fish sauce.

848
01:00:40,007 --> 01:00:43,046
- Look.
- Singto.

849
01:00:44,576 --> 01:00:45,780
Go find Dad, quick.

850
01:00:47,482 --> 01:00:50,846
Good job. Good job, boy.

851
01:00:58,531 --> 01:01:00,710
Singto, come to Mom.

852
01:01:02,258 --> 01:01:04,132
Come to Mom, sweetheart?

853
01:01:10,230 --> 01:01:12,562
Singto, listen to me.

854
01:01:12,925 --> 01:01:13,843
This person

855
01:01:15,812 --> 01:01:19,749
is your mom. Go give her a hug, okay?

856
01:01:19,749 --> 01:01:20,648
Can you do that?

857
01:01:22,445 --> 01:01:27,071
Oh, come on. How is he supposed
to warm up to Wai?

858
01:01:27,071 --> 01:01:30,493
- She's never raised or cared for him.
- Mom.

859
01:01:35,138 --> 01:01:37,069
I'm sorry, Mom.

860
01:01:39,535 --> 01:01:42,899
I'm truly sorry for leaving
everything behind.

861
01:01:43,186 --> 01:01:48,443
Back then, I didn't know what to do,
so I did something stupid like that.

862
01:01:50,947 --> 01:01:52,476
I'm sorry.

863
01:01:53,738 --> 01:01:54,828
Mom.

864
01:01:55,478 --> 01:01:57,313
Wai's back now, no matter what.

865
01:01:57,313 --> 01:02:00,027
- Don't be mad at her, Mom.
- Yeah.

866
01:02:00,180 --> 01:02:02,417
Still ganging up on her like before.

867
01:02:05,073 --> 01:02:06,278
Sorry.

868
01:02:08,094 --> 01:02:11,344
Alright then, come back home.

869
01:02:12,682 --> 01:02:14,288
So Singto can get used to
having you around.

870
01:02:17,002 --> 01:02:19,124
- Let's go.
- Thank you, Mom.

871
01:02:22,833 --> 01:02:24,439
Thank you.

872
01:02:25,949 --> 01:02:27,936
- Don't run away again.
- Okay.

873
01:02:28,472 --> 01:02:29,409
Mm.

874
01:02:31,569 --> 01:02:34,704
- I'm sorry, Mom.
- Just come back and live with us.

875
01:02:37,590 --> 01:02:38,833
Come back and be with him.

876
01:02:41,261 --> 01:02:42,637
I'm sorry.

877
01:02:43,459 --> 01:02:46,422
- Taking her side again.
- Oh, Mom.

878
01:02:46,422 --> 01:02:48,334
- She made a real effort to come back.
- Yeah.

879
01:02:52,252 --> 01:02:56,745
Thank you so much. And Krit,
thank you very much.

880
01:02:57,356 --> 01:02:58,255
It's nothing.

881
01:02:58,561 --> 01:03:00,491
I'll wait outside, then.

882
01:03:00,797 --> 01:03:02,938
- So you two can talk for a bit.
- Sure.

883
01:03:06,188 --> 01:03:07,717
- Hey.
- Hmm?

884
01:03:07,717 --> 01:03:10,929
You've got yourself a great boyfriend.
Hold on to him.

885
01:03:10,929 --> 01:03:12,343
Don't make the same mistake I did.

886
01:03:12,343 --> 01:03:15,096
And don't make Krit sad, okay?

887
01:03:15,402 --> 01:03:18,269
Before you go sticking your nose
into my business,

888
01:03:18,575 --> 01:03:21,213
you should get your own life
together first, Wai.

889
01:03:25,285 --> 01:03:26,145
Wai.

890
01:03:28,573 --> 01:03:30,293
I don't want to see you hurting anymore.

891
01:03:33,256 --> 01:03:35,111
Yeah, rest assured.

892
01:03:36,372 --> 01:03:38,227
I won't make the same mistake twice.

893
01:03:40,157 --> 01:03:41,495
- I'm heading out.
- Go pack your things.

894
01:03:55,871 --> 01:03:56,712
Sigh.

895
01:03:59,790 --> 01:04:02,657
My sister's still as stubborn as ever.

896
01:04:15,274 --> 01:04:16,918
Now that Wai's back home.

897
01:04:19,192 --> 01:04:21,161
You should move into my place
full-time now, Wayu.

898
01:04:23,436 --> 01:04:28,120
It's close to work, and I'd get to take
better care of you too.

899
01:04:32,363 --> 01:04:33,396
Um...

900
01:04:34,772 --> 01:04:36,779
I do want to move in with you,

901
01:04:37,754 --> 01:04:38,672
but...

902
01:04:39,627 --> 01:04:41,157
I'm worried about Singto.

903
01:04:47,255 --> 01:04:49,491
It's not like I'm stopping you
from coming back here.

904
01:04:51,747 --> 01:04:52,818
Besides,

905
01:04:53,238 --> 01:04:54,806
if you stay here all the time,

906
01:04:55,436 --> 01:04:57,597
how will Singto ever get used to Wai?

907
01:05:01,362 --> 01:05:05,090
Then I can move into the condo too.

908
01:05:05,931 --> 01:05:07,250
- Really?
- Yeah.

909
01:05:09,946 --> 01:05:11,895
Which room is yours? I'll help you pack.

910
01:05:11,895 --> 01:05:13,272
Hey, wait, Krit.

911
01:05:13,272 --> 01:05:16,808
You don't have to rush it. We can wait.

912
01:05:17,152 --> 01:05:18,586
- I want to see it. Is it this room?
- Krit, you don't have to...

913
01:05:18,586 --> 01:05:20,746
- Is it this one? The room on the left?
- No, really, there's no need to rush.

914
01:05:27,513 --> 01:05:28,201
Ugh.

915
01:05:29,138 --> 01:05:32,923
Whoa. You can move some of my stuff
out first. I barely use it anyway.

916
01:05:33,860 --> 01:05:36,937
Sorry, I've got kind of a lot of stuff.

917
01:05:39,958 --> 01:05:42,749
This is just a little of it, actually.
I already feel bad.

918
01:05:44,240 --> 01:05:45,158
Mm.

919
01:05:45,769 --> 01:05:47,317
Then if you brought everything over,

920
01:05:47,317 --> 01:05:49,841
I'd probably have to buy another room
just for your clothes.

921
01:05:49,841 --> 01:05:54,123
Come on, that's an exaggeration.
It's not that bad, is it?

922
01:05:54,123 --> 01:05:55,021
Oh.

923
01:05:57,086 --> 01:05:58,309
I'm serious.

924
01:05:59,781 --> 01:06:01,425
If our relationship
gets to a certain point,

925
01:06:02,840 --> 01:06:04,006
I want to buy a house.

926
01:06:05,229 --> 01:06:07,045
Somewhere with plenty of space.

927
01:06:07,695 --> 01:06:09,320
I want a walk-in closet.

928
01:06:10,524 --> 01:06:14,711
A home theater. A gym.

929
01:06:18,649 --> 01:06:20,579
Honestly, I used to think that too.

930
01:06:21,421 --> 01:06:23,887
I used to think that once I graduated,

931
01:06:24,536 --> 01:06:27,136
I'd design a house for my family,

932
01:06:28,130 --> 01:06:33,846
which my mom, Wai,
and Singto would all love.

933
01:06:36,083 --> 01:06:37,918
So, when do you plan
to go back to school?

934
01:06:39,963 --> 01:06:41,167
Not anytime soon.

935
01:06:42,028 --> 01:06:44,953
For now, I want to focus on work first.

936
01:06:44,953 --> 01:06:47,705
Singto's getting older too.

937
01:06:47,705 --> 01:06:49,387
I'm going to need a lot more money.

938
01:06:51,108 --> 01:06:52,064
Then...

939
01:06:52,828 --> 01:06:54,893
What if I funded your education?

940
01:06:58,200 --> 01:07:00,284
Then how am I supposed to pay you back?

941
01:07:01,239 --> 01:07:04,967
No, I can't do that.
You'd just be losing out.

942
01:07:05,655 --> 01:07:08,026
Who said you had to
pay me back in money?

943
01:07:10,606 --> 01:07:14,257
Hmm. Aren't you sly?

944
01:07:15,443 --> 01:07:19,744
Mm... Let me think about it first.

945
01:07:20,795 --> 01:07:22,496
I just don't want to be a burden.

946
01:07:24,293 --> 01:07:25,612
What burden?

947
01:07:26,014 --> 01:07:29,091
Once you graduate,
you can design our house.

948
01:07:30,143 --> 01:07:33,393
That's a great deal for me.
I'd have my own personal architect.

949
01:07:37,522 --> 01:07:39,911
Hey, I've got something to show you.

950
01:07:41,173 --> 01:07:42,358
Here.

951
01:07:44,576 --> 01:07:46,889
Look at this.

952
01:07:47,596 --> 01:07:48,838
(Posts)
Look at the old ones.

953
01:07:53,140 --> 01:07:54,095
Mm.

954
01:07:57,249 --> 01:07:58,549
You're pretty good at this too.

955
01:07:59,811 --> 01:08:00,748
Look at this one.

956
01:08:02,564 --> 01:08:03,577
Mm.

957
01:08:05,565 --> 01:08:06,444
And then?

958
01:08:07,706 --> 01:08:11,128
Do you have any dreams,

959
01:08:11,625 --> 01:08:13,211
like real dreams of your own?

960
01:08:18,984 --> 01:08:19,959
Not really.

961
01:08:21,852 --> 01:08:23,094
I guess...

962
01:08:24,547 --> 01:08:26,344
I'll become a cop, like my dad wants.

963
01:08:28,084 --> 01:08:31,181
Right now, I just want to catch criminals
and make society a little better.

964
01:08:32,767 --> 01:08:37,584
Wow, that sounds like such
a media-trained answer.

965
01:08:38,674 --> 01:08:41,982
Don't you have any other dreams?
Anything at all? Hmm?

966
01:08:48,289 --> 01:08:49,589
Honestly, I do.

967
01:08:51,348 --> 01:08:53,317
I'm just not sure
if they'll sound too childish.

968
01:08:54,923 --> 01:08:55,802
What are they?

969
01:09:01,460 --> 01:09:03,296
I just want to keep
being with you on and on.

970
01:09:04,710 --> 01:09:08,036
Until we're sitting there
plucking each other's gray hairs.

971
01:09:09,566 --> 01:09:10,407
Hehe.

972
01:09:12,930 --> 01:09:14,478
That sounds so old.

973
01:09:15,339 --> 01:09:16,926
I mean it.

974
01:09:19,143 --> 01:09:21,093
I want to be with you forever.

975
01:09:43,019 --> 01:09:43,917
Sir.

976
01:09:44,663 --> 01:09:46,135
Our informant reported that

977
01:09:46,135 --> 01:09:48,907
the suspect is hiding out around Silom.

978
01:09:51,659 --> 01:09:52,921
Silom again?

979
01:09:55,693 --> 01:09:57,413
Set up checkpoints around the area.

980
01:09:58,618 --> 01:10:01,906
And pull the CCTV footage
from that alley.

981
01:10:02,498 --> 01:10:04,620
If the suspect is still hiding there,

982
01:10:05,652 --> 01:10:09,189
I'm sure they must've gone
in and out of that alley before.

983
01:10:10,240 --> 01:10:11,177
Yes, sir.

984
01:10:22,016 --> 01:10:24,386
The CCTV footage is ready, Inspector.

985
01:10:24,845 --> 01:10:25,934
Thanks a lot.

986
01:11:09,271 --> 01:11:09,997
(Directed by Banchorn Vorasataree)

987
01:11:09,997 --> 01:11:14,547
♪I love you with all my heart,
and I'm ready to give you everything♪

988
01:11:14,547 --> 01:11:19,326
♪All one life can offer♪

989
01:11:19,402 --> 01:11:24,512
♪I won't leave you behind,
no matter what I face♪

990
01:11:24,736 --> 01:11:27,756
♪No matter how bad♪

991
01:11:27,871 --> 01:11:32,535
♪I give you my all,
my body and everything♪

992
01:11:32,630 --> 01:11:37,390
♪Please trust your life
with someone like me♪

993
01:11:37,524 --> 01:11:42,016
♪I assure you there's no one♪

994
01:11:42,240 --> 01:11:47,789
♪Could ever love you more than I do♪

995
01:11:49,109 --> 01:11:51,232
♪No one♪

996
01:11:51,328 --> 01:11:57,271
♪Could ever love you more than I do♪

997
01:11:58,017 --> 01:12:00,288
♪No one♪

998
01:12:00,352 --> 01:12:05,778
♪Could ever love you more than I do♪

999
01:12:06,963 --> 01:12:09,863
♪No one♪

1000
01:12:09,863 --> 01:12:15,660
♪Could ever love you more than I do♪

1001
01:12:15,948 --> 01:12:18,378
♪No one♪

1002
01:12:18,378 --> 01:12:23,250
♪Could ever love you more than I do♪

1003
01:12:35,790 --> 01:12:40,340
♪Like a poem, heartache♪

1004
01:12:40,340 --> 01:12:44,966
♪Won't stay with us for long,
but will slowly fade away♪

1005
01:12:44,966 --> 01:12:50,299
♪You came into my life
and carried me away♪

1006
01:12:50,299 --> 01:12:53,778
♪To something I never expected♪

1007
01:12:53,778 --> 01:12:58,634
♪To truly understand
a love beyond reason♪

1008
01:12:58,634 --> 01:13:03,183
♪When I found someone like you♪

1009
01:13:03,183 --> 01:13:08,364
♪My whole life no longer
has to keep dreaming♪

1010
01:13:08,364 --> 01:13:12,053
♪Now that you're right here♪

1011
01:13:12,053 --> 01:13:16,756
♪I love you with all my heart,
